## XR Interaction Toolkit Patterns

### Interactable Setup

```csharp
// Always use XRBaseInteractable as the base
[RequireComponent(typeof(Rigidbody))]
public class VRGrabbable : XRGrabInteractable
{
    protected override void OnSelectEntered(SelectEnterEventArgs args)
    {
        base.OnSelectEntered(args);
        // Custom grab logic
    }
}
```

### Locomotion Setup

```csharp
// XR Origin setup with locomotion
[RequireComponent(typeof(XROrigin))]
public class VRRig : MonoBehaviour
{
    [SerializeField] private TeleportationProvider _teleportProvider;
    [SerializeField] private ContinuousMoveProvider _moveProvider;
    
    // Use comfort vignette for continuous movement
    [SerializeField] private TunnelingVignetteController _vignette;
}
```

### Input Action Reference Pattern

```csharp
// Use InputActionReference for cross-platform input
[SerializeField] private InputActionReference _gripAction;
[SerializeField] private InputActionReference _triggerAction;

private void OnEnable()
{
    _gripAction.action.performed += OnGrip;
    _gripAction.action.Enable();
}
```

## VR Comfort Guidelines

- **Frame rate**: Target 72fps minimum (90fps preferred)
- **Locomotion**: Default to teleportation; continuous movement opt-in
- **Vignette**: Apply tunneling during artificial movement
- **Snap turn**: Use 45° or 30° increments, not smooth rotation by default
- **UI Distance**: Keep UI at 1-2m distance from user
- **Text Size**: Minimum 0.5m height at 2m distance
- **Motion**: Avoid moving the camera without user input

## Local Validation Commands

Run these before creating a PR:

```bash
# Unity Editor validation (run from project root)
Unity -batchmode -projectPath . -executeMethod Editor.BuildScript.ValidateProject -quit -logFile -

# C# formatting
dotnet format --verify-no-changes

# Run tests
Unity -batchmode -projectPath . -runTests -testPlatform PlayMode -logFile - -quit
```

## Platform Build Commands

```bash
# Quest/Android build
Unity -batchmode -projectPath . -buildTarget Android -executeMethod BuildScript.BuildQuest -quit

# Windows VR build (SteamVR/Oculus PC)
Unity -batchmode -projectPath . -buildTarget Win64 -executeMethod BuildScript.BuildPC -quit
```

